HEADWORD: Cabriolet
<hw>Cab`ri*o*let"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., dim. of
<ets>cabriole</ets> a leap, caper, from It. <ets>capriola</ets>, fr.
dim. of L. <ets>caper</ets> he-goat, <ets>capra</ets> she-goat. This
carriage is so called from its skipping lightness. Cf. <er>Cab</er>,
<er>Caper</er> a leap.]</ety> <def>A one-horse carriage with two seats
and a calash top.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cabrit</ent>⟦br⟧
